FL,385,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38402
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F384A1780513862
OL,3,CGuernsey's #45 million surplus masks
OL,4,Cunderlying deficit
OL,6,FOverall, the full States of Guernsey
OL,7,FGroup - which controls Guernsey
OL,8,FElectricity, Guernsey Post, Aurigny,
OL,9,Fthe Ports, Guernsey Water, and the
OL,10,FGuernsey Housing Association -
OL,11,Freported a surplus of #106m in 2025.
OL,13,FOne of the biggest increases was in
OL,14,Fincome tax revenues, which #39 million
OL,15,Fcame from the introduction of the
OL,16,FOECD's Pillar 2 scheme.
OL,18,FThose taxes aim to ensure that
OL,19,Fmultinational businesses pay a minimum
OL,20,F15% effective tax rate.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G2/6
OL,2,W+.!/*%/*%/*%/*%+,"-$ /(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BCh Is News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,385,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38403
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F384A1780513862
OL,3,CGuernsey's #45 million surplus masks
OL,4,Cunderlying deficit
OL,6,FHowever, this is just an estimation,
OL,7,Fas Pillar 2 amounts will not be
OL,8,Fcollected until the middle of 2027.
OL,10,FThe main increases:
OL,12,FDespite the increases and surpluses,
OL,13,Fthere is still a funding gap of #50
OL,14,Fmillion - down from #58 million in
OL,15,F2024.
OL,17,FGovernment spending on infrastructure
OL,18,Fand other projects meant that cash
OL,19,Fbalances actually fell by #9 million.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G3/6
OL,2,W+.!/*%/*%/*%/*%+,"-$ /(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BCh Is News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,385,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38404
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F384A1780513862
OL,3,CGuernsey's #45 million surplus masks
OL,4,Cunderlying deficit
OL,6,FOther spending outliers included a
OL,7,F#16.5 million bill for cleaning up
OL,8,Fhistoric firefighting foam (PFAS) at
OL,9,FGuernsey Airport and an operating loss
OL,10,Fof #6.3 million for Aurigny as the
OL,11,Fairline dealt with increased demand.
OL,13,FIt means that once all other factors
OL,14,Fare taken into account, the underlying
OL,15,Ffinancial position of the States
OL,16,Fremains in deficit.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G4/6
OL,2,W+.!/*%/*%/*%/*%+,"-$ /(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BCh Is News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,385,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38405
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F384A1780513862
OL,3,CGuernsey's #45 million surplus masks
OL,4,Cunderlying deficit
OL,6,FDeputy Lindsay de Sausmarez, the
OL,7,FPresident of the Policy & Resources
OL,8,FCommittee, says: "It feels a bit
OL,9,Fparadoxical that there's a funding
OL,10,Fgap, or structural deficit, when the
OL,11,F2025 Accounts show a surplus, but
OL,12,Fthat's because they're two different
OL,13,Fthings.
OL,15,F"Two things can be true at the same
OL,16,Ftime, and this is a good example: it's
OL,17,Fgreat that we have an accounting
OL,18,Fsurplus for 2025, but when we look at
OL,19,Fthat bigger picture, we've still got a
OL,20,Fshortfall, or funding gap."
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G5/6
OL,2,W+.!/*%/*%/*%/*%+,"-$ /(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,
